    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-03T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-03T19:00:00-05:00" n="885"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d885">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.0146/7–2544: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-03T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 3, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1036. 1. With reference to Chinese desire that a three-power conference be
                    convened to settle question of military government in territories recaptured
                    from the Japanese, these problems are being given careful study and
                    consideration. (ReEmbs 1289, July 25, 3 p.m.)</p>
                <p>2. Department hopes to be able to clear at an early date with the highest
                    officers of the Government the conclusions we have reached and will then
                    communicate with you further.</p>
                <p>3. In your discretion you may inform Dr. Soong of the foregoing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
